1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:02,040
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:03,780
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:06,480
(Episode 6)

4
00:00:06,540 --> 00:00:08,650
What? What are you talking about?

5
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:10,380
What do you mean
you're not coming back?

6
00:00:11,420 --> 00:00:12,520
Look, honey.

7
00:00:13,420 --> 00:00:14,590
Leaving? Where are you going?

8
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:21,260
Please try to understand, honey.

9
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:24,130
Of course, I understand, honey.
I always do.

10
00:00:25,530 --> 00:00:27,370
Thank you for understanding.

11
00:00:27,570 --> 00:00:30,200
In that case,
I guess this is goodbye.

12
00:00:30,840 --> 00:00:31,970
Bye.

13
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:33,670
Hello?

14
00:00:34,770 --> 00:00:36,980
Hello? Honey?

15
00:00:37,340 --> 00:00:38,480
Was that Hui Gyeong?

16
00:00:41,550 --> 00:00:42,550
Mom.

17
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:44,350
What did she say?

18
00:00:45,420 --> 00:00:48,390
- What?
- What did she say?

19
00:00:49,150 --> 00:00:51,120
It was nothing.

20
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:54,890
She said she met Seong Mi.
Mom, what are you doing here?

21
00:00:55,090 --> 00:00:56,490
The realtor called.

22
00:00:56,490 --> 00:00:58,730
The deposit for your new place
hasn't come through.

23
00:00:59,030 --> 00:01:02,770
No way. Hui Gyeong said last night
that she'd go to the realtor...

24
00:01:03,070 --> 00:01:06,540
and pay it. Let me call the realtor.

25
00:01:06,810 --> 00:01:09,510
Son, is something wrong?

26
00:01:09,770 --> 00:01:11,840
Come on, Mom. Nothing's wrong.

27
00:01:11,910 --> 00:01:14,150
When have I ever given you
a reason to worry?

28
00:01:14,510 --> 00:01:17,820
I have to pop out for a bit, Mom.
The brace for Ms. Lee Chun Ja.

29
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:21,320
I said I'd show her how to use it.
I'll be right back.

30
00:01:28,660 --> 00:01:31,630
The phone is currently off.
Connecting to voicemail.

31
00:01:31,630 --> 00:01:33,670
- Please leave a message after...
- Gosh, this is driving me crazy.

32
00:01:35,070 --> 00:01:37,100
- Mr. Gong.
- Yes.

33
00:01:37,170 --> 00:01:38,970
- No answer?
- No, it's off.

34
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,410
Nurse Oh, how much of that
did my mom hear?

35
00:01:42,510 --> 00:01:44,510
"Of course, I understand, honey.
I always do."

36
00:01:44,780 --> 00:01:46,080
From around that part.

37
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:49,480
She didn't hear the part about her
not coming back or leaving.

38
00:01:49,580 --> 00:01:51,020
Man, I'm losing my mind.

39
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:53,520
What on earth is going on?

40
00:01:54,150 --> 00:01:55,350
Do you think maybe...

41
00:01:56,050 --> 00:01:58,160
she got caught up
in a voice phishing scam?

42
00:01:58,290 --> 00:01:59,290
What?

43
00:01:59,290 --> 00:02:02,090
It happens a lot these days.
People click on one fake link,

44
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:04,530
get their phone hacked,
and lose their life savings.

45
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:08,330
- Your wife's a little naive.
- Right, I... My gosh.

46
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:11,440
My brain is short-circuiting.
My goodness, what should I do?

47
00:02:11,540 --> 00:02:15,540
What do you mean?
You should contact our go-to cop,

48
00:02:15,610 --> 00:02:20,040
- Officer Jung!
- Right, yes. I'm on my way.

49
00:02:20,380 --> 00:02:22,950
- I'll see you in a bit.
- Yes, see you!

50
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:29,950
What? When did you see her last?
What about your last call?

51
00:02:30,050 --> 00:02:33,930
I saw her briefly this morning
when she was leaving for Seoul.

52
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:37,860
The last time we spoke was...
Thirty minutes ago.

53
00:02:39,930 --> 00:02:42,970
- Thirty minutes ago?
- Yes. Please hurry.

54
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:48,240
- Hurry. Trace her location.
- Well...

55
00:02:48,310 --> 00:02:49,470
Look.

56
00:02:49,910 --> 00:02:52,940
I know you worry about your wife.
I really do.

57
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:57,380
Running a trace after 30 minutes
is a bit of a stretch, right?

58
00:02:57,450 --> 00:02:58,880
What do you mean,
"a bit of a stretch?"

59
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:03,090
This isn't like her. She called,
said strange things, and hung up!

60
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:05,260
And when I called back,
her phone was off.

61
00:03:05,390 --> 00:03:08,530
It could be a voice phishing scam!

62
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:13,230
Hui Gyeong got our security deposit
from my sister-in-law today.

63
00:03:13,230 --> 00:03:16,470
- In cash! It was all in cash!
- Cash?

64
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:19,400
Yes. And now that
I'm thinking about it,

65
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:22,070
it's strange that she'd want
that large sum in cash.

66
00:03:22,140 --> 00:03:24,180
It felt like someone was there,
threatening her.

67
00:03:24,380 --> 00:03:27,280
She suddenly said she was leaving.
Yes, it was so sudden!

68
00:03:27,450 --> 00:03:31,250
Deposit in cash, loss of contact,
possible voice phishing.

69
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:34,120
It's a scary world out there, Chief.

70
00:03:34,490 --> 00:03:37,320
Please. I'm begging you.
Help me, please.

71
00:03:37,390 --> 00:03:40,160
Try not to worry.
I'll do everything I can to help.

72
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:43,160
- Help with what?
- Sir?

73
00:03:43,230 --> 00:03:46,260
Calm down. Let's wait a bit longer.

74
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:50,600
How can I wait? In my shoes, Chief,
could you really just wait?

75
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:55,140
Fine. If you're that insistent,
why not go to her work and ask?

76
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,240
Right.

77
00:03:58,310 --> 00:04:00,610
Officer Jung.
Please, I'm begging you.

78
00:04:01,110 --> 00:04:02,210
You have to find her. Please.

79
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:05,220
Yes, sir, I understand.
Let me know if you learn more.

80
00:04:05,380 --> 00:04:07,090
Okay, I will. Yes.

81
00:04:07,090 --> 00:04:08,950
(Reliable Police)

82
00:04:11,260 --> 00:04:15,660
I'm sorry, what did you just say?
The designer rentals aren't back?

83
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:17,560
No one was home?

84
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:20,430
That can't be. My brother-in-law
was supposed to be here.

85
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:23,640
All right, I get it.
I'll call you back.

86
00:04:28,970 --> 00:04:30,070
Auntie.

87
00:04:30,610 --> 00:04:32,840
Hey, Ji Hu. Yes.

88
00:04:33,580 --> 00:04:35,980
- Have you seen your dad?
- No.

89
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:37,380
Why? Is something wrong with Dad?

90
00:04:37,850 --> 00:04:40,050
What? Well...

91
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,050
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

92
00:04:43,050 --> 00:04:46,760
Hey, son.
How did your English test go?

93
00:04:49,430 --> 00:04:52,400
Really? Good job!

94
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:57,200
Go ask your aunt for a snack.
No cookies or anything like that.

95
00:04:57,270 --> 00:04:59,640
Tell her to give you
something with protein.

96
00:05:00,140 --> 00:05:03,140
Mom, have you heard from Dad
at all today?

97
00:05:03,710 --> 00:05:06,140
No. Your dad's on a business trip,
remember? Why?

98
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:07,610
It's just that...

99
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:12,280
- I think Dad took Aunt's things.
- Ji Hu, please.

100
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:16,220
What? What do you mean by that?
Are you sure?

101
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:20,630
Hey, Dong Suk.

102
00:05:20,890 --> 00:05:23,190
What in the world
did you say to him?

103
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:26,700
What's missing that makes you think
my husband took them?

104
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,870
Go upstairs and study. Go on.

105
00:05:33,710 --> 00:05:36,640
No, it's not like that.
I asked your husband...

106
00:05:36,710 --> 00:05:39,210
to return some designer things
I'd rented.

107
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:43,250
They say the items weren't returned,
and I can't find them in the house.

108
00:05:43,610 --> 00:05:45,380
And his phone is off.

109
00:05:45,950 --> 00:05:49,750
What? He's on a business trip.
Of course, his phone might be off.

110
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:52,360
Ji Hu's dad went to a building site
in Jecheon.

111
00:05:52,420 --> 00:05:56,590
He went there to sign a contract
for a bulk plan for foreign workers!

112
00:05:56,660 --> 00:06:00,200
How dare you call him a thief
to his son without any facts?

113
00:06:00,470 --> 00:06:02,100
Why don't you try looking for them
properly first?

114
00:06:02,830 --> 00:06:04,570
What's with all the shouting?

115
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:06,570
Who's accusing someone
of being a thief?

116
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:08,810
Your sister-in-law?
Accusing your husband?

117
00:06:08,870 --> 00:06:11,610
That's right. She says
her designer rentals are lost.

118
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:13,640
And she's implying
that Ji Hu's dad stole them.

119
00:06:14,110 --> 00:06:16,510
- Are you sure he didn't steal them?
- Dad!

120
00:06:16,580 --> 00:06:18,480
Yes. He probably sold them off...

121
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:20,950
- and went to gamble it all away.
- I told you, no!

122
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:23,920
If he gets into trouble again,
I'm kicking all of you out. Got it?

123
00:06:25,220 --> 00:06:28,190
Just kick them out?
If he actually stole something,

124
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:32,060
I'll have him jailed for theft.
That jerk.

125
00:06:33,830 --> 00:06:37,000
Gosh, I can't believe you guys.
Seriously.

126
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:47,080
The phone is currently turned off
and will be forwarded to voicemail.

127
00:06:47,310 --> 00:06:49,210
Charges will apply after the tone...

128
00:06:50,450 --> 00:06:53,180
No way. It can't be true.

129
00:06:54,620 --> 00:06:55,750
No way.

130
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:04,600
What do you mean, lost?
I couldn't have lost them.

131
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:07,370
And even if they are, I can just
pay for them in full, right?

132
00:07:08,730 --> 00:07:12,100
What? Forty thousand dollars?

133
00:07:14,470 --> 00:07:15,540
It's covered by insurance, right?

134
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:18,480
Come on, just kidding.

135
00:07:19,010 --> 00:07:23,080
I'll wire you the extra fee now.
Okay.

136
00:07:24,820 --> 00:07:27,650
Oh, no. What am I going to do?

137
00:07:32,190 --> 00:07:34,730
Ta-da!

138
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:39,930
Sweetie, if you keep this up,
your dad will take your credit card.

139
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:44,700
I only spent what I was allowed to.
That's why I couldn't buy a purse.

140
00:07:44,770 --> 00:07:48,540
- So?
- Let me borrow the limited edition.

141
00:07:48,610 --> 00:07:50,110
I want to take it
on my date with Woo Jae.

142
00:07:51,780 --> 00:07:54,380
What? Don't even try to stop me.
It's no use.

143
00:07:54,450 --> 00:07:55,850
The heart wants what it wants!

144
00:07:56,010 --> 00:07:57,650
We'll see about that.
We'll see if I can stop you.

145
00:07:57,950 --> 00:08:01,450
Did you know Woo Jae's older sister
works at Taehan?

146
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:03,550
His sister works at Taehan?

147
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:06,160
So when they said
"a designer at a big company,"

148
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,860
they meant Taehan.

149
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:10,230
Darn, what a useless complication.

150
00:08:10,330 --> 00:08:14,500
What a weird coincidence.
The same department as my brother.

151
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,030
What? The same department?

152
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:18,670
You didn't know?
My brother is a fashion director.

153
00:08:19,340 --> 00:08:21,310
I bet they went to the workshop
together today.

154
00:08:23,710 --> 00:08:26,240
My brother had a huge crush on her
before he went to study abroad.

155
00:08:26,310 --> 00:08:30,480
- I hope they hit it off.
- What? What did you say?

156
00:08:30,550 --> 00:08:33,850
If she and my brother get together,
and I get together with Woo Jae...

157
00:08:34,290 --> 00:08:36,550
My gosh, we'd be double in-laws!

158
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:39,320
Are you serious? Don't say that.
You're unbelievable!

159
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:41,590
- How about some pork belly tonight?
- Get out.

160
00:08:41,590 --> 00:08:43,290
I could go
for some skin-on pork belly, too.

161
00:08:43,860 --> 00:08:44,860
Neener!

162
00:08:52,470 --> 00:08:53,540
What is this?

163
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:07,590
Surprise!

164
00:09:09,290 --> 00:09:11,120
It took some effort
to book this place.

165
00:09:11,290 --> 00:09:14,730
Season 2 of "3 Days and 2 Nights."

166
00:09:14,790 --> 00:09:18,160
This house was featured
in Episode 35. Isn't it cool?

167
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:21,300
Well, this doesn't exactly look like
a five-star hotel.

168
00:09:22,030 --> 00:09:24,170
Come on, a workshop
at some predictable hotel...

169
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:27,200
or resort is no fun, you know?

170
00:09:27,810 --> 00:09:31,840
- I happen to like "predictable."
- And I dressed for a luxury hotel.

171
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:35,380
I was excited, thinking
we'd have a buffet breakfast.

172
00:09:36,110 --> 00:09:38,850
Still, it's got a certain charm.

173
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:44,760
I guess so. It has its charms.

174
00:09:45,620 --> 00:09:48,760
See? Didn't I tell you it'd be
beyond your wildest imagination?

175
00:09:49,090 --> 00:09:52,630
So, what's the plan for food?
Should I look up good places nearby?

176
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:55,870
Come on, what's the whole point
of a workshop?

177
00:09:56,700 --> 00:10:00,770
- To build some solid teamwork?
- Exactly.

178
00:10:01,270 --> 00:10:03,770
Which is why I've prepared...

179
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:07,950
- a cook-off!
- What?

180
00:10:08,210 --> 00:10:10,950
You'll split into two teams to cook,
and I'll be the judge.

181
00:10:11,220 --> 00:10:13,820
There isn't a penalty
for the losing team...

182
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:16,720
or something like that, is there?

183
00:10:17,020 --> 00:10:19,920
- I have a bad feeling there is.
- Don't tell me...

184
00:10:20,190 --> 00:10:21,190
We have to sleep outside?

185
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:24,200
- Oh, bingo!
- Shoot!

186
00:10:26,830 --> 00:10:28,470
Right. Our team uniforms.

187
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:30,300
Come on over here.

188
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:31,600
Team uniforms?

189
00:10:37,710 --> 00:10:38,840
All right.

190
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:41,980
I've prepared these...

191
00:10:41,980 --> 00:10:44,050
for the full countryside
getaway experience.

192
00:10:44,420 --> 00:10:46,880
This is
what you'd call "granny-chic."

193
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:49,220
All right, get changed
and come back out.

194
00:10:49,950 --> 00:10:52,560
I can't wear this.
There's absolutely no way.

195
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:53,920
I'm going home.

196
00:10:54,190 --> 00:10:55,290
Come on, let's go.

197
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:57,060
Come on.

198
00:11:00,300 --> 00:11:01,500
Come on, what's wrong?

199
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:06,140
- It's kind of cute.
- What is this?

200
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:08,910
Hey, was he always like this?

201
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:11,880
I don't think
he was this over-the-top.

202
00:11:12,910 --> 00:11:15,010
I wonder what they were feeding him
while he was abroad.

203
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:23,920
My gosh!

204
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:30,130
What do you think?
It's cozy and quaint, right?

205
00:11:30,930 --> 00:11:34,730
Wow, even this unique country smell
is perfect.

206
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:55,790
Do we really have to wear these?

207
00:11:56,350 --> 00:11:57,620
Ms. Gong.

208
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:02,930
For crying out loud.

209
00:12:15,110 --> 00:12:17,640
Wow, you guys look great.

210
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:20,280
You're all pros,
so the fit is on another level.

211
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:21,680
What do you think?

212
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:24,050
And they're super comfortable
to move in, right?

213
00:12:24,650 --> 00:12:27,220
Speaking as a professional
and looking purely at practicality,

214
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:30,960
the stretch, airflow, and comfort
are the perfect trifecta.

215
00:12:31,790 --> 00:12:32,790
I knew you'd see it.

216
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:36,130
All right, everyone must be hungry.

217
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:37,760
So let's get started.

218
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:39,600
Are we going to buy groceries?

219
00:12:39,930 --> 00:12:41,670
We have to source our ingredients
ourselves.

220
00:12:42,070 --> 00:12:44,800
- In the middle of winter?
- Out here in the middle of nowhere?

221
00:12:45,140 --> 00:12:48,040
Actually,
over there in that greenhouse,

222
00:12:48,110 --> 00:12:50,440
we have permission to take
and eat whatever we find there.

223
00:12:50,510 --> 00:12:54,010
Okay, so that's the vegetables,
but what about protein?

224
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:56,780
Don't tell me you're going to
make us butcher a pig.

225
00:12:57,010 --> 00:12:59,020
Well, you're close.

226
00:13:00,050 --> 00:13:01,720
No way.

227
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:12,260
Behold... Ice fishing!

228
00:13:12,330 --> 00:13:16,270
Ice fishing!

229
00:13:19,070 --> 00:13:22,170
See? This is what
self-sufficiency is all about.

230
00:13:22,410 --> 00:13:24,210
Let's catch ourselves
some fresh protein.

231
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:28,680
The feel of the catch on the line,
the thrill running through you...

232
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,610
I've always wanted to experience it.
You know?

233
00:13:31,980 --> 00:13:33,950
Should we just make a run for it?

234
00:13:35,690 --> 00:13:38,090
Or maybe we should
go hide somewhere?

235
00:13:40,260 --> 00:13:41,860
Does anyone have a tranquilizer gun?

236
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:44,230
All right, let's go!

237
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:48,370
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

238
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:53,970
(Habi Hair Salon)

239
00:13:58,680 --> 00:14:00,340
Hui Gyeong quit.

240
00:14:00,950 --> 00:14:02,310
She quit? When?

241
00:14:02,650 --> 00:14:05,220
The day before yesterday?
Or maybe the day before that?

242
00:14:05,620 --> 00:14:07,280
Anyway, she quit all of a sudden.

243
00:14:07,550 --> 00:14:09,850
I thought she was planning
to open her own salon,

244
00:14:10,390 --> 00:14:13,720
since she was looking for a spot
right after getting her license.

245
00:14:14,460 --> 00:14:16,130
She got her license?
What do you mean?

246
00:14:16,530 --> 00:14:19,360
She got it a while back.
Didn't she tell you?

247
00:14:19,930 --> 00:14:22,370
But she always said she was going
to her class or to study.

248
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,200
Where on earth has she been going
all this time?

249
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:27,870
Gosh, Hui Gyeong.

250
00:14:28,510 --> 00:14:30,870
What are you hiding from me?

251
00:14:32,010 --> 00:14:33,780
Why are you doing this to me?
Really.

252
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:37,110
Did I do something wrong?

253
00:14:38,020 --> 00:14:39,920
There must be something.
Gosh, this is driving me crazy.

254
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:41,720
Hui Gyeong!

255
00:14:46,090 --> 00:14:47,790
(All Carriers Welcome)

256
00:14:54,370 --> 00:14:56,970
Welcome. Looking to get a new phone?

257
00:14:58,140 --> 00:14:59,400
No, that's not why I'm here.

258
00:15:00,670 --> 00:15:03,940
I'm Min Yong Gil's wife.

259
00:15:04,540 --> 00:15:06,580
Well, what's gotten into him?

260
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:07,850
What?

261
00:15:07,850 --> 00:15:09,610
He was a no-show,
and his phone was off,

262
00:15:09,610 --> 00:15:11,150
so I figured something was wrong.

263
00:15:11,220 --> 00:15:12,620
But then, I came in this morning
and saw...

264
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:15,550
that all of the new merchandise
was completely gone.

265
00:15:16,420 --> 00:15:17,660
You've got to be kidding me.

266
00:15:18,290 --> 00:15:21,190
You're saying
my husband took all of it?

267
00:15:21,290 --> 00:15:25,460
Yes. I checked the CCTV.
He came last night and took it all!

268
00:15:25,860 --> 00:15:28,300
How could he just stab me
in the back like this?

269
00:15:28,970 --> 00:15:33,100
Tell him to bring it all back
immediately, or I'll call the cops.

270
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:52,360
My income covers our living costs,
and the money your dad earns...

271
00:15:52,420 --> 00:15:55,230
We're saving it for your tutoring
and college tuition.

272
00:16:01,470 --> 00:16:02,700
(Min Yong Gil, In-branch Withdrawal:
35,286 dollars)

273
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:07,940
(Balance: 0.78 dollars,
Onjeong Branch)

274
00:16:29,290 --> 00:16:32,360
The phone is currently turned off.
Connecting to voicemail.

275
00:16:32,430 --> 00:16:33,500
Charges will apply after the tone...

276
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,370
- Mom.
- Hi.

277
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:39,670
- Yes, hey.
- Hi.

278
00:16:39,670 --> 00:16:41,510
So? Have you heard from Hui Gyeong?

279
00:16:41,970 --> 00:16:46,680
Yes. She said she got a call.
Her aunt got ill, apparently.

280
00:16:46,910 --> 00:16:48,750
Is that what happened?

281
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:53,220
Yes. She rushed her to the hospital,
so she wasn't thinking straight.

282
00:16:53,650 --> 00:16:57,320
I see. So what's wrong with her?
Is she doing okay now?

283
00:16:58,090 --> 00:17:01,760
Well, her blood...
I guess she has high blood pressure.

284
00:17:01,830 --> 00:17:04,230
Anyway, I'm planning to visit her
early tomorrow morning.

285
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:08,500
You should. I'll get some vitamins
and supplements later,

286
00:17:08,570 --> 00:17:09,970
so you can give them to her
tomorrow.

287
00:17:10,070 --> 00:17:12,270
Okay, I will.
And Mom, one more thing.

288
00:17:12,540 --> 00:17:14,570
I called the realtor
and sorted everything out.

289
00:17:15,270 --> 00:17:18,040
Since the house is vacant, they said
it's fine if we're a few days late.

290
00:17:18,140 --> 00:17:20,440
Good. That's a relief.

291
00:17:20,940 --> 00:17:24,480
I'm going to head to bed.
I have to catch the first train.

292
00:17:24,550 --> 00:17:25,780
Mom, I'm turning in.

293
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:55,510
Hui Gyeong.

294
00:18:02,450 --> 00:18:03,450
This is driving me nuts.

295
00:18:11,230 --> 00:18:12,230
Are you sure?

296
00:18:13,260 --> 00:18:14,770
You're sure he didn't get into
some trouble again?

297
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:18,040
I'm telling you, he didn't.
I found them and sent them back.

298
00:18:18,370 --> 00:18:21,770
Honestly, you.
I almost blamed him for nothing.

299
00:18:22,070 --> 00:18:23,110
I know, right?

300
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:25,040
Why won't you take it?

301
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:29,480
Put that on and see Dr. Gong.
Ask him about the VP job.

302
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:31,220
I said, forget it.

303
00:18:33,150 --> 00:18:35,590
Fine, then I'm canceling
your golf game.

304
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:38,390
And forget about
running for city council, too.

305
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:43,760
Do you want me
to help you with that?

306
00:18:47,730 --> 00:18:48,930
Can't you just ask him?

307
00:18:49,470 --> 00:18:51,670
Didn't you say
you'd do anything for me?

308
00:18:52,170 --> 00:18:56,510
Oh, I could, sure.
But you know what he'd say, right?

309
00:18:56,710 --> 00:18:59,240
"What kind of man
hides behind his wife's skirt?"

310
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:01,780
He'd say that and then some.
That jerk.

311
00:19:02,910 --> 00:19:06,650
Plus, he'd tell Dr. Han Seong Mi,
wouldn't he?

312
00:19:08,950 --> 00:19:10,020
Help me with my jacket.

313
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:14,260
The embarrassment
will only last a moment.

314
00:19:14,260 --> 00:19:16,530
You get what you want by asking.

315
00:19:16,590 --> 00:19:19,030
It won't be the last time
we have to swallow our pride.

316
00:19:19,330 --> 00:19:23,600
But that guy... He won't make me VP
unless I get on my knees and beg.

317
00:19:23,630 --> 00:19:26,970
Honey. There's a way
to get the same result...

318
00:19:27,370 --> 00:19:31,440
without actually having to do it.
I'll show you how.

319
00:19:32,340 --> 00:19:33,340
What's that?

320
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:42,320
What's up?
You stopped me on my way out,

321
00:19:42,350 --> 00:19:44,120
so spit it out.

322
00:19:45,820 --> 00:19:47,520
I know I'm sitting down right now,

323
00:19:48,460 --> 00:19:50,260
but could you pretend I'm kneeling?

324
00:19:50,730 --> 00:19:54,360
- What?
- If I knelt, they'd stare at you,

325
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:57,430
and that would be awkward for you,
wouldn't it?

326
00:19:57,630 --> 00:20:01,840
Wow, you're seeing things now?
Who else is here? No one's here.

327
00:20:05,010 --> 00:20:06,010
Right.

328
00:20:07,010 --> 00:20:09,250
So you want me to...

329
00:20:09,580 --> 00:20:11,780
make you the Vice President
of the Merchants' Association?

330
00:20:12,150 --> 00:20:16,450
- Yes.
- Why? To pad your council resume?

331
00:20:16,790 --> 00:20:17,820
Yes.

332
00:20:17,890 --> 00:20:22,130
Hey, you fool!
Then you should've won the election!

333
00:20:22,190 --> 00:20:24,160
Man, this guy...

334
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:26,460
He won by one vote,

335
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:29,530
and now he's so full of himself.

336
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:32,200
Oh, man. I can hear you, you know.

337
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:33,640
Hey, come on.

338
00:20:34,340 --> 00:20:35,440
I'm asking for a favor here.

339
00:20:37,670 --> 00:20:42,210
Fine.
Then you'll do as I say, right?

340
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:44,880
Of course.

341
00:20:46,420 --> 00:20:50,950
Do morning exercises every day
and facility safety checks. Can you?

342
00:20:51,020 --> 00:20:52,020
Of course.

343
00:20:52,660 --> 00:20:54,860
Go on patrol in your spare time,

344
00:20:54,930 --> 00:20:57,830
and handle every civil complaint
that comes in.

345
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:59,200
Of course.

346
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:03,230
Oh, and on weekends,
you have to help at busy shops,

347
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:06,870
volunteer for the lunchbox program,
and visit seniors living alone.

348
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,610
You'll attend the merchant forums,
executive meetings,

349
00:21:09,670 --> 00:21:12,040
and the general assemblies too,
right?

350
00:21:12,810 --> 00:21:14,040
Of course.

351
00:21:15,510 --> 00:21:18,420
- You promise?
- Yes. I promise.

352
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:21,490
- Hey, you don't trust me?
- Right. I don't.

353
00:21:21,550 --> 00:21:24,150
Then what? What do you want from me?

354
00:21:24,350 --> 00:21:25,990
What, you want me to sign
a written pledge or something?

355
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:27,360
Kneel.

356
00:21:27,860 --> 00:21:30,360
- What?
- Why? You can't do it?

357
00:21:30,590 --> 00:21:33,200
- Hey, you son of a...
- All right.

358
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:35,000
The exit is that way.

359
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:37,370
Why would I leave?

360
00:21:43,110 --> 00:21:44,570
I'm all yours.

361
00:21:45,980 --> 00:21:48,610
All right, okay. Fine. You got it.

362
00:21:50,180 --> 00:21:51,180
Thanks, man.

363
00:21:53,820 --> 00:21:56,350
I really didn't think
you'd actually kneel, though.

364
00:21:56,690 --> 00:21:58,860
- I'm surprised.
- Hey, it's a great leg workout.

365
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:00,360
Hey.

366
00:22:01,060 --> 00:22:02,290
As your old friend,

367
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:04,160
do me one favor.

368
00:22:04,490 --> 00:22:07,560
What?
Not to tell Seong Mi about this?

369
00:22:08,330 --> 00:22:10,100
- Yes.
- All right.

370
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:13,140
I know you've had a thing
for Seong Mi since way back,

371
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:17,540
so I'll let you save a little pride,
man to man.

372
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:19,340
Thanks.

373
00:22:21,180 --> 00:22:22,180
I'm counting on you, then.

374
00:22:27,820 --> 00:22:30,850
Really?
Bucket actually got on his knees?

375
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:34,620
Yes.
Man, he must have been desperate.

376
00:22:35,990 --> 00:22:39,760
This has his wife written
all over it.

377
00:22:40,460 --> 00:22:42,730
I know, right?
Even to me, it was clear...

378
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:47,140
- someone told him to do it.
- They're quite the pair.

379
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:50,910
I did it. I pulled it off.
This is for us.

380
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:54,210
Honey, well done.

381
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:56,980
Soon, you'll be
a city council member.

382
00:22:56,980 --> 00:22:58,180
- Right?
- Yes.

383
00:22:58,550 --> 00:23:00,750
But you managed to do it
without kneeling, right?

384
00:23:00,820 --> 00:23:03,190
Come on. Jeong Han is a pushover.

385
00:23:03,450 --> 00:23:06,190
Your husband is
very capable and resourceful.

386
00:23:06,260 --> 00:23:07,720
Didn't you know
you married such an amazing man?

387
00:23:07,790 --> 00:23:11,460
- Of course. It's why I married you.
- Of course...

388
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:16,170
Anyway,
don't you worry about a thing.

389
00:23:16,370 --> 00:23:17,670
Just go ahead and schedule
your golf games.

390
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:19,670
You bet.

391
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:21,510
Well done, honey.

392
00:23:23,670 --> 00:23:26,810
Ji Hu, you must be hungry.
I'll make you a late-night snack.

393
00:23:26,980 --> 00:23:28,450
I'm okay, Auntie.

394
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:31,450
Really? Then can I get you
something to drink?

395
00:23:31,850 --> 00:23:34,280
I was just getting my mom
a glass of cold water.

396
00:23:35,590 --> 00:23:37,190
I'm worried she'll get dehydrated.

397
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:39,360
From crying so much.

398
00:23:46,060 --> 00:23:47,330
How could he do this?

399
00:23:48,730 --> 00:23:53,270
How could he do this again?
How are Ji Hu and I going to live?

400
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:56,670
This is just too much. It really is.

401
00:24:20,860 --> 00:24:22,800
I thought she was packing
for our move,

402
00:24:25,140 --> 00:24:26,870
but it looks like she only took
her own things.

403
00:24:27,940 --> 00:24:29,640
Hui Gyeong, why on earth?

404
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:34,240
Who could that be?

405
00:24:36,950 --> 00:24:38,650
Hello? Hui Gyeong, is that you?

406
00:24:40,280 --> 00:24:41,920
Yes, Officer Jung.

407
00:24:43,020 --> 00:24:45,290
No, I haven't heard from her.
I still haven't found her.

408
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:47,090
(Onjeong Police Substation)

409
00:24:47,190 --> 00:24:50,090
Mr. Gong.
I have the day off tomorrow.

410
00:24:50,230 --> 00:24:53,130
So, about looking for your wife,
if you don't mind,

411
00:24:53,560 --> 00:24:56,200
could I help you on my own time?

412
00:24:56,470 --> 00:24:57,470
Really?

413
00:24:58,700 --> 00:25:01,200
Yes, I would be so grateful
if you would.

414
00:25:01,810 --> 00:25:05,210
To be honest, I was frustrated
because I had no one to talk to.

415
00:25:07,710 --> 00:25:09,280
Thank you, Officer Jung.

416
00:25:10,180 --> 00:25:12,550
Yes. Thank you.

417
00:25:23,030 --> 00:25:24,030
Here you go.

418
00:25:26,300 --> 00:25:29,370
Your dad and your sister
have never once been like this,

419
00:25:29,470 --> 00:25:32,600
so who on earth do you take after
to be so sweet, son?

420
00:25:32,670 --> 00:25:34,140
I guess I take after my uncle.

421
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:39,210
By the way, Ju Ah let me know
she got to her workshop okay.

422
00:25:39,980 --> 00:25:42,350
Of course, she'd call you,
but not me.

423
00:25:43,780 --> 00:25:44,880
Right, Gong Woo Jae!

424
00:25:45,620 --> 00:25:49,450
Why do you have to use my full name?
It's scary.

425
00:25:49,550 --> 00:25:52,920
Did you know Bucket's son and Ju Ah
work at the same company?

426
00:25:53,220 --> 00:25:54,990
Yes, I did.

427
00:25:55,060 --> 00:25:57,260
And you didn't even tell me.
The nerve of you two.

428
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:58,900
Wait, are you talking about...

429
00:25:59,330 --> 00:26:02,330
the grandson from the herbal clinic
who studied abroad?

430
00:26:02,370 --> 00:26:05,900
Yes. But apparently,
he pretends not to know Ju Ah.

431
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:09,410
Why? What? Has it been so long
that he doesn't remember her?

432
00:26:10,340 --> 00:26:14,810
Our families are tangled
in odd ways, even the kids.

433
00:26:16,110 --> 00:26:17,110
You.

434
00:26:17,510 --> 00:26:20,580
Stay away from their daughter.
Got it?

435
00:26:21,180 --> 00:26:24,890
Stay away? Please.
Their granddaughter wants Woo Jae.

436
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:27,220
- What's he supposed to do?
- Exactly.

437
00:26:27,290 --> 00:26:31,730
It takes two to tango.
So watch yourself.

438
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:35,130
- And draw a clear line. Understand?
- Yes, I heard you.

439
00:26:36,430 --> 00:26:37,630
Hey, just eat.

440
00:26:40,100 --> 00:26:41,710
I'm going to my room.

441
00:26:41,810 --> 00:26:45,080
Hey, wait. You're just leaving
after peeling all this?

442
00:26:49,780 --> 00:26:52,580
What took you so long?
I was about to raid your house.

443
00:26:52,580 --> 00:26:53,620
Why?

444
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:56,550
What do you mean, why?
We have a date to plan.

445
00:26:56,620 --> 00:26:58,150
We need to make plans.

446
00:26:58,560 --> 00:27:01,890
Hey, Eun Bin. Did you tell
anyone in your family about it?

447
00:27:02,330 --> 00:27:05,330
What? No.

448
00:27:05,700 --> 00:27:07,500
You can't tell them. Ever.

449
00:27:07,560 --> 00:27:12,300
Don't worry. We pinky promised
as our first physical contact.

450
00:27:12,370 --> 00:27:13,700
As if I would ever tell.

451
00:27:14,140 --> 00:27:15,710
You call that physical contact?

452
00:27:15,970 --> 00:27:20,080
Hey, it's not that complicated.
If we touched, it counts.

453
00:27:21,280 --> 00:27:24,710
You know my brother and your sister
work at the same company, right?

454
00:27:24,710 --> 00:27:27,020
Yes,
and your parents know that, right?

455
00:27:27,080 --> 00:27:30,620
Of course. My stepmom's already
throwing a fit about it.

456
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:32,190
Woo Jae.

457
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:35,830
I have a new wish. And that is...

458
00:27:35,890 --> 00:27:39,030
- Double in-laws!
- What?

459
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:43,100
My brother marries your sister,
and you and I get married...

460
00:27:44,030 --> 00:27:47,170
Hey! Gosh, I can't believe
he just hung up on me.

461
00:27:48,610 --> 00:27:52,980
If that actually happened,
my stepmom would lose her mind.

462
00:27:54,210 --> 00:27:58,950
I get giddy just thinking about it.
Double in-laws!

463
00:28:01,250 --> 00:28:05,120
You call this a relaxing getaway?
This is just hard labor.

464
00:28:05,490 --> 00:28:09,490
Come on! What are you talking about?
This is as real as relaxation gets.

465
00:28:10,090 --> 00:28:12,830
Do you know what it takes
for something like this in the city?

466
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:16,070
You have to book a farm experience,
fight through all the traffic,

467
00:28:16,130 --> 00:28:19,570
pay an admission fee,
and rent boots and a trowel.

468
00:28:19,670 --> 00:28:23,770
- All just to dig up one potato.
- Right.

469
00:28:23,910 --> 00:28:28,850
Look at us. An authentic location
with a real farm and real labor.

470
00:28:28,910 --> 00:28:31,080
A spicy stew
with green onions and potatoes...

471
00:28:31,080 --> 00:28:32,980
you dug yourself in the cold winter.

472
00:28:33,080 --> 00:28:36,590
That's not just a spicy stew.
It's soul-stirring stew.

473
00:28:36,690 --> 00:28:39,320
Gosh, why did I even open my mouth?

474
00:28:39,360 --> 00:28:42,490
That soul-stirring stew
defines real local food,

475
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:45,360
and the ultimate rural food therapy,
wouldn't you agree?

476
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:47,430
Now, let's go prep these.
What do you say?

477
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:54,540
How on earth
did he become such a chatterbox?

478
00:28:56,540 --> 00:28:59,610
- Hurry up, Ms. Gong!
- Yes, I'm coming.

479
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:02,110
He must have eaten something weird.

480
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:21,630
Shouldn't we go help them?

481
00:29:22,030 --> 00:29:23,570
No, let them have their moment.

482
00:29:25,470 --> 00:29:26,470
Let's just take a break.

483
00:29:29,210 --> 00:29:30,210
Man, it's cold.

484
00:29:30,470 --> 00:29:32,240
I'm tired, but still...

485
00:29:36,810 --> 00:29:38,520
So you don't just like to eat.

486
00:29:38,780 --> 00:29:40,120
It looks like
you're a good cook, too.

487
00:29:41,150 --> 00:29:42,150
You too, Ms. Gong.

488
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:45,920
I felt you'd be good at anything
you do with your hands.

489
00:29:49,230 --> 00:29:53,060
You're talking like
you knew me in the past.

490
00:29:56,270 --> 00:29:58,370
Was I?

491
00:30:13,620 --> 00:30:16,890
Gosh, you guys are the worst.
Couldn't you just start the fire?

492
00:30:17,190 --> 00:30:19,920
Hey, the firewood was too damp.
It wouldn't catch.

493
00:30:20,060 --> 00:30:22,190
Then you could've at least tried
to dry it out.

494
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:25,090
That's what I suggested.

495
00:30:26,700 --> 00:30:28,300
Gosh, honestly...

496
00:30:31,070 --> 00:30:32,070
Sorry.

497
00:30:37,970 --> 00:30:38,980
Unbelievable.

498
00:30:39,510 --> 00:30:42,780
Sorry. I meant to lie down
for a second but passed out.

499
00:30:43,180 --> 00:30:44,550
It's fine. I'll take care of it.

500
00:30:44,910 --> 00:30:47,580
So what if the firewood is damp?
You think it won't catch fire?

501
00:30:48,450 --> 00:30:51,690
Director, it's getting really late.
Why don't we just order in?

502
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:54,890
No. We started this,
so we have to see it through.

503
00:30:56,190 --> 00:30:57,190
All right.

504
00:30:59,030 --> 00:31:01,760
- What do we do? Director!
- No, it's fine. Just let him.

505
00:31:02,100 --> 00:31:04,230
Just wait.
We're already running late,

506
00:31:05,030 --> 00:31:06,100
so let's just let him do his thing.

507
00:31:12,610 --> 00:31:15,310
- What should we do?
- He's unstoppable.

508
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:36,600
Gosh, I'm starving.

509
00:31:38,940 --> 00:31:40,570
- Oh, wait...
- Ms. Gong.

510
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:43,570
Isn't he being way too stubborn?

511
00:31:43,770 --> 00:31:47,240
Can't we just order
some jjajangmyeon or something?

512
00:31:53,980 --> 00:31:54,980
Come on.

513
00:32:02,490 --> 00:32:03,530
Gosh, it's freezing.

514
00:32:04,890 --> 00:32:07,360
- This is all the newspaper we have.
- Oh, yes.

515
00:32:08,060 --> 00:32:09,230
Thanks.

516
00:32:09,230 --> 00:32:11,630
Honestly,
this isn't going to work, is it?

517
00:32:12,840 --> 00:32:15,670
Tell me about it.
Nothing's going according to plan.

518
00:32:17,070 --> 00:32:21,180
This is part of the fun of a trip.
The smoke's making my eyes water.

519
00:32:22,580 --> 00:32:23,650
Should we just call it a day?

520
00:32:24,380 --> 00:32:26,350
No way. We have to see this through.

521
00:32:27,350 --> 00:32:30,720
You go in and get some rest.
I started this, so I'll finish it.

522
00:32:32,720 --> 00:32:34,820
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

523
00:32:35,890 --> 00:32:36,890
Good luck, then.

524
00:32:43,670 --> 00:32:45,700
- Oh, boy.
- All right.

525
00:32:54,180 --> 00:32:55,180
My goodness.

526
00:33:08,730 --> 00:33:09,730
This hits the spot.

527
00:33:11,930 --> 00:33:12,930
Oh, my.

528
00:33:27,680 --> 00:33:29,410
We could seriously sell this.

529
00:33:30,450 --> 00:33:33,550
Ms. Gong is the one
who got the seasoning just right.

530
00:33:36,420 --> 00:33:39,960
Honestly, I thought it'd be a bust
and we'd starve.

531
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:43,530
Me, too. Honestly,
you really surprised me, Director.

532
00:33:43,660 --> 00:33:45,860
Same here. I would've just given up,

533
00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:48,560
but you were incredibly persistent.

534
00:33:49,670 --> 00:33:52,070
I'm just glad it all worked out.

535
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:55,470
Otherwise,
I'd have looked like a fool.

536
00:33:57,440 --> 00:33:59,310
- Team Leader.
- Yes?

537
00:34:00,140 --> 00:34:02,250
Oh, I meant Ms. Gong.

538
00:34:02,710 --> 00:34:05,650
- Oh, yes.
- Use surnames to avoid confusion.

539
00:34:05,780 --> 00:34:06,780
Why, you...

540
00:34:06,850 --> 00:34:11,590
Hey, instead of that,
why don't we all just go by "Pro?"

541
00:34:12,090 --> 00:34:14,260
Right.
There are only a few of us anyway.

542
00:34:14,660 --> 00:34:16,990
Besides, what kind of leader am I
if I don't even have a team?

543
00:34:17,590 --> 00:34:19,200
Would that be all right
with you, Director?

544
00:34:19,760 --> 00:34:24,630
I've always felt our formal titles
can create a sense of distance.

545
00:34:25,270 --> 00:34:28,600
If it encourages everyone
to be a top pro in their role...

546
00:34:30,310 --> 00:34:34,380
- I'm fine with it.
- All right then, Pro Gong!

547
00:34:34,640 --> 00:34:36,310
Pro Jo Seong Min.

548
00:34:36,950 --> 00:34:38,210
- Cheers!
- And Pro Kim!

549
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:40,650
- What is it, Pro Jo?
- Hey, Pro Shin!

550
00:34:40,720 --> 00:34:42,250
Pro Choi!

551
00:34:45,090 --> 00:34:46,090
Hang on a second.

552
00:34:47,060 --> 00:34:49,090
If that's the spirit behind it,

553
00:34:49,490 --> 00:34:51,860
does that mean we can call you
Pro Yang, Director?

554
00:34:52,030 --> 00:34:55,030
My goodness. Absolutely not.

555
00:34:57,470 --> 00:35:00,170
All right, everyone!
What a great night.

556
00:35:00,870 --> 00:35:02,410
To all of us... Cheers!

557
00:35:03,040 --> 00:35:06,440
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

558
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:15,790
- Director, let me pour you a drink.
- Thanks.

559
00:35:16,420 --> 00:35:18,920
- You worked so hard today.
- Thank you.

560
00:35:19,420 --> 00:35:21,420
- Let me pour you one, too.
- Sure.

561
00:35:22,290 --> 00:35:23,290
Here you go.

562
00:35:23,790 --> 00:35:25,290
I should've helped you out more.

563
00:35:26,430 --> 00:35:29,700
<i>- Time for our favorite random game</i>
<i>- Hey!</i>

564
00:35:29,700 --> 00:35:32,200
<i>- What's the game? Game on</i>
<i>- What's the game? Game on</i>

565
00:35:33,100 --> 00:35:34,640
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

566
00:35:34,900 --> 00:35:36,340
- Introduce yourselves!
- Introduce yourselves!

567
00:35:37,070 --> 00:35:38,070
I'm Strawberry!

568
00:35:38,540 --> 00:35:39,540
I'm Lemon!

569
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:40,880
Watermelon, two!

570
00:35:41,140 --> 00:35:42,210
Watermelon, watermelon!

571
00:35:42,580 --> 00:35:44,610
- Grapes, four!
- Grapes...

572
00:35:45,980 --> 00:35:47,520
This is nice.
It has a great atmosphere.

573
00:35:48,750 --> 00:35:50,950
I'm happy.

574
00:35:52,860 --> 00:35:55,260
Director, you have this energy...

575
00:35:56,030 --> 00:35:57,630
It's so bright and positive.

576
00:35:58,060 --> 00:36:02,870
- I do?
- Yes. You're always so positive,

577
00:36:02,930 --> 00:36:04,930
optimistic, and cheerful.

578
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:09,810
Your whole approach to life,
or your philosophy, I guess...

579
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:12,280
Whatever it is,
I really envy you for that.

580
00:36:16,580 --> 00:36:18,950
This is just between you and me,
Pro Park.

581
00:36:20,180 --> 00:36:21,350
The truth is, a long time ago...

582
00:36:22,720 --> 00:36:24,150
I was a total crybaby.

583
00:36:25,350 --> 00:36:26,360
Really?

584
00:36:27,990 --> 00:36:30,490
Come on,
I find that hard to believe.

585
00:36:31,230 --> 00:36:32,930
No, I'm serious.

586
00:36:34,300 --> 00:36:36,100
Back then, I was so miserable,

587
00:36:37,370 --> 00:36:39,600
it felt like my whole world
was crashing down.

588
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:45,470
I was so lonely and wretched,
and felt like I'd lost everything.

589
00:36:46,640 --> 00:36:49,880
I felt so helpless,
like there was nothing I could do,

590
00:36:50,550 --> 00:36:51,610
so I cried every day.

591
00:36:55,550 --> 00:36:56,750
But one day,

592
00:36:57,350 --> 00:36:59,690
someone said this to me.

593
00:37:00,460 --> 00:37:01,920
It was the adults' fault.

594
00:37:02,460 --> 00:37:03,830
It's not your fault.

595
00:37:07,130 --> 00:37:08,700
And then, guess what?

596
00:37:09,430 --> 00:37:10,930
That person bought me a pork cutlet.

597
00:37:12,840 --> 00:37:14,670
Pork cutlet? Now, that's love.

598
00:37:27,420 --> 00:37:28,420
Yes.

599
00:37:29,290 --> 00:37:30,520
- All right.
- Wait a minute, hold on.

600
00:37:31,190 --> 00:37:33,590
Was it a woman
who bought you the pork cutlet?

601
00:37:35,560 --> 00:37:36,560
Yes.

602
00:37:37,630 --> 00:37:39,300
And then, on the day I left Korea,

603
00:37:42,270 --> 00:37:43,570
she sang me a song.

604
00:37:44,730 --> 00:37:47,870
<i>I have been so lonely</i>
<i>and had such a hard time</i>

605
00:37:48,500 --> 00:37:52,240
<i>But it's only a rehearsal</i>

606
00:37:53,980 --> 00:37:57,510
<i>I'm not going to fall down</i>

607
00:37:58,080 --> 00:37:59,520
<i>I got this</i>

608
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:00,650
Goodbye, Yang Hyun Bin.

609
00:38:01,550 --> 00:38:03,620
Make sure you come back happy.

610
00:38:04,320 --> 00:38:05,320
Okay?

611
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:08,760
I made a resolution then and there.

612
00:38:09,560 --> 00:38:12,830
I had to be happy.
I would never cry again.

613
00:38:12,900 --> 00:38:15,600
So that if I ever met her again
someday,

614
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:19,370
she would praise me
for having lived a good life.

615
00:38:27,710 --> 00:38:28,740
So for me,

616
00:38:29,350 --> 00:38:33,020
that one thought drove me
to work hard at being happy.

617
00:38:37,190 --> 00:38:39,460
Did you meet her again
after returning to Korea?

618
00:38:42,590 --> 00:38:43,860
What was it like seeing her again?

619
00:38:44,530 --> 00:38:45,590
Do you still have feelings for her?

620
00:38:49,070 --> 00:38:50,070
I do.

621
00:38:51,530 --> 00:38:52,540
Cheers.

622
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:06,820
This is nice.

623
00:39:34,610 --> 00:39:37,150
Dae Han.
Weren't you taking the first train?

624
00:39:37,350 --> 00:39:38,350
Time to get up.

625
00:39:43,020 --> 00:39:44,020
Dae Han.

626
00:39:48,460 --> 00:39:50,230
Gosh, he's already left.

627
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:52,230
I told him
to take the supplements with him.

628
00:40:00,470 --> 00:40:01,840
What on earth is this?

629
00:40:04,010 --> 00:40:06,510
Hey, Jeong Han.
You must've heard from Mom.

630
00:40:07,580 --> 00:40:08,740
Aunt will be okay.

631
00:40:10,580 --> 00:40:11,780
Sorry to make you worry, Jeong Han.

632
00:40:12,750 --> 00:40:13,780
Don't be.

633
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:16,650
All right. Just travel safe, okay?

634
00:40:18,050 --> 00:40:19,290
- Nurse Oh.
- Yes?

635
00:40:19,290 --> 00:40:21,690
Can you contact the part-timer
who came the other day...

636
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:24,930
and reschedule
today's manual therapy appointments?

637
00:40:25,130 --> 00:40:26,130
Got it.

638
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:28,360
Why? Is something wrong?

639
00:40:28,900 --> 00:40:30,070
Why isn't Mr. Gong coming in?

640
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:33,570
Apparently, his wife's aunt
is not feeling well.

641
00:40:34,870 --> 00:40:37,040
What? That can't be right.

642
00:40:38,510 --> 00:40:42,380
And where is this guy?
He hasn't even shown up. Goodness.

643
00:40:42,650 --> 00:40:43,650
Who are you talking about?

644
00:40:44,580 --> 00:40:46,350
Gosh, seriously.

645
00:40:47,980 --> 00:40:51,820
The bike-share data breach
was found late last month.

646
00:40:52,390 --> 00:40:54,820
The Seoul Facilities Corp. was sued
for violating data privacy...

647
00:40:54,820 --> 00:40:56,290
Goodness, what now?

648
00:41:00,560 --> 00:41:01,860
Hey, Dr. Gong.

649
00:41:02,500 --> 00:41:05,940
Hey! What are you doing?
Get your butt over here now!

650
00:41:06,200 --> 00:41:10,510
I didn't sleep a wink last night.
I was coughing all night.

651
00:41:11,910 --> 00:41:16,480
The election stressed me out.
I've come down with a bug.

652
00:41:16,580 --> 00:41:18,410
(Onjeong Market)

653
00:41:18,510 --> 00:41:21,980
What? You're the one who brags
about never even catching a cold,

654
00:41:22,050 --> 00:41:25,290
so how come you don't take
your family's herbal medicine?

655
00:41:25,620 --> 00:41:29,390
I know, right?
But I can't get other people sick.

656
00:41:29,460 --> 00:41:30,460
Right?

657
00:41:34,560 --> 00:41:35,930
Gosh, I have to go.
I feel like I'm dying.

658
00:41:40,140 --> 00:41:43,770
Ouch, that hurts!
Dad! What was that for?

659
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:45,740
If you're going to do something,
do it right, you pathetic fool!

660
00:41:45,880 --> 00:41:48,680
Who said I wasn't going to?
I'll do it!

661
00:41:49,180 --> 00:41:51,050
I was just messing around.

662
00:41:51,450 --> 00:41:52,450
Get a move on!

663
00:41:52,650 --> 00:41:55,120
Dad, I just told him I couldn't go
because I'm not feeling well.

664
00:41:55,820 --> 00:41:57,550
If I show up now,
I'll look like a fool.

665
00:41:59,760 --> 00:42:01,890
What? Wait, is that for real?

666
00:42:02,290 --> 00:42:03,690
Hey, hush.

667
00:42:04,460 --> 00:42:07,260
But why give the VP position
to Dr. Yang?

668
00:42:07,430 --> 00:42:09,970
If that was the plan,
why bother running in the election?

669
00:42:10,370 --> 00:42:13,100
Well, I only won by one vote.

670
00:42:13,340 --> 00:42:15,400
It means support is evenly split,
don't you think?

671
00:42:15,640 --> 00:42:20,610
I figured if I gave him the VP spot,
I could also absorb his pledges.

672
00:42:20,740 --> 00:42:23,680
But you didn't predict
he'd just blow off work like this?

673
00:42:25,010 --> 00:42:26,220
Of course, I did.

674
00:42:26,680 --> 00:42:30,690
But I came fully prepared,
so don't you worry.

675
00:42:31,390 --> 00:42:32,390
Prepared, how?

676
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:36,760
- Father, come and eat. You, too.
- All right.

677
00:42:46,900 --> 00:42:49,040
Man, this guy doesn't give up.

678
00:42:49,970 --> 00:42:50,970
What's this?

679
00:42:51,370 --> 00:42:56,380
Get here right now, or I can't say
how far this video will spread.

680
00:42:56,750 --> 00:42:58,550
What is he talking about?
What video?

681
00:42:58,750 --> 00:43:01,220
(Unfair Gong Jeong Han)

682
00:43:07,260 --> 00:43:08,590
That crazy jerk!

683
00:43:09,160 --> 00:43:11,760
No, no way. What do I do?

684
00:43:12,060 --> 00:43:13,200
Oh, no!

685
00:43:13,200 --> 00:43:16,000
Two, two, three, four.

686
00:43:16,430 --> 00:43:19,870
Dr. Yang! Hurry up and join us.
Come on.

687
00:43:20,100 --> 00:43:21,900
Okay, let's do some waist exercises.
Put your hands on your hips.

688
00:43:21,970 --> 00:43:26,010
All right. One, two, three, four.

689
00:43:27,810 --> 00:43:32,080
Seven, eight. One foot forward,

690
00:43:32,150 --> 00:43:36,320
and finger hearts.
One, two, three, four,

691
00:43:36,390 --> 00:43:40,060
five, six, seven, eight.
Switch feet.

692
00:43:40,320 --> 00:43:42,830
Two, two, three, four,

693
00:43:42,890 --> 00:43:47,360
five, six, seven, eight.
Great job, everyone.

694
00:43:48,500 --> 00:43:52,500
All right, have a healthy
and prosperous day!

695
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:54,540
See you all tomorrow morning!

696
00:43:56,740 --> 00:43:57,740
Good work, everyone.

697
00:43:59,070 --> 00:44:02,210
- Hey, Gong Jeong Han.
- What? I thought you were sick.

698
00:44:02,780 --> 00:44:04,280
Wow, you have a healthy glow.

699
00:44:04,710 --> 00:44:06,920
Delete the video.

700
00:44:07,220 --> 00:44:08,220
No.

701
00:44:08,520 --> 00:44:10,220
Hey, I really was sick!

702
00:44:11,120 --> 00:44:13,490
What kind of Korean medicine doctor
lies about being sick?

703
00:44:13,690 --> 00:44:16,530
Do you have no ethics
as a medical professional?

704
00:44:16,630 --> 00:44:19,760
Hey, threatening me
with CCTV footage...

705
00:44:20,200 --> 00:44:24,270
- is blatant blackmail. Got it?
- Is it? Then feel free to back out.

706
00:44:24,930 --> 00:44:29,040
I arranged for your VP certificate.
I guess I should call and cancel.

707
00:44:29,410 --> 00:44:31,170
- Wait.
- Right.

708
00:44:31,440 --> 00:44:35,210
The local paper wants
an exclusive interview with us.

709
00:44:35,340 --> 00:44:37,010
I'd better cancel that, too.

710
00:44:37,150 --> 00:44:38,780
All right, fine! I get it.

711
00:44:39,480 --> 00:44:41,750
I'll work my butt off for you,

712
00:44:42,480 --> 00:44:43,790
so just don't release that video.
All right?

713
00:44:44,090 --> 00:44:45,090
Okay.

714
00:44:46,160 --> 00:44:47,420
Look at that.
You're looking even healthier now.

715
00:44:47,860 --> 00:44:50,560
Let's head out
for our morning patrol!

716
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:56,330
Morning! Hope you sell a lot
and have a great day!

717
00:44:59,330 --> 00:45:01,640
Man, I'm so curious.

718
00:45:02,300 --> 00:45:04,040
I don't think
her aunt is actually sick.

719
00:45:06,510 --> 00:45:07,510
Nurse Oh.

720
00:45:08,140 --> 00:45:09,810
Are you talking about
Hui Gyeong's aunt?

721
00:45:10,610 --> 00:45:11,810
Do you know something?

722
00:45:12,250 --> 00:45:13,820
No.

723
00:45:14,450 --> 00:45:16,920
I meant my aunt.

724
00:45:29,130 --> 00:45:31,430
Take care of yourself, Aunt.

725
00:45:32,000 --> 00:45:33,540
I'll come visit again sometime.

726
00:45:33,970 --> 00:45:36,740
Tell that brat, Hui Gyeong,
to call me once in a while.

727
00:45:37,210 --> 00:45:39,270
I know she's uneducated, but still.

728
00:45:39,580 --> 00:45:43,910
How could she just cut me off
after I raised her?

729
00:45:44,410 --> 00:45:45,410
Okay.

730
00:45:59,430 --> 00:46:01,800
- Can you please hurry up?
- I'm all done.

731
00:46:02,200 --> 00:46:03,770
Are you just going to keep
spraying this with water?

732
00:46:04,130 --> 00:46:07,140
- You need to scrub it.
- When I do a job, I do it right.

733
00:46:07,200 --> 00:46:10,240
You heard the Director and me
talking last night, didn't you?

734
00:46:11,070 --> 00:46:14,240
You knew I heard you and asked him
if he still liked me. Is that it?

735
00:46:15,380 --> 00:46:17,380
Not exactly.

736
00:46:18,180 --> 00:46:19,180
Anyway, you're grateful, aren't you?

737
00:46:19,680 --> 00:46:23,150
I guess a guy really can't
ever forget his first love.

738
00:46:23,790 --> 00:46:25,650
That was just the alcohol talking.

739
00:46:25,920 --> 00:46:28,020
And you, stop acting like
you know everything.

740
00:46:28,960 --> 00:46:29,960
Man...

741
00:46:30,430 --> 00:46:35,300
To think you made the crybaby
so bright and positive.

742
00:46:35,430 --> 00:46:37,870
- Shut it, will you?
- When I do a job, I do it right.

743
00:46:38,000 --> 00:46:41,000
Besides, he has a girlfriend.

744
00:46:41,070 --> 00:46:45,010
Hey. You're glad he's back, right?
You find him attractive.

745
00:46:45,610 --> 00:46:48,080
Whatever. Unbelievable.

746
00:46:48,940 --> 00:46:52,050
- Come on, let's really scrub this.
- Is there another sponge?

747
00:46:52,450 --> 00:46:54,550
- I don't know.
- Here you go, So Hye.

748
00:46:56,590 --> 00:46:57,750
It's a little kitty cat. Meow.

749
00:46:59,190 --> 00:47:00,190
Meow.

750
00:47:00,890 --> 00:47:01,890
Meow.

751
00:47:11,270 --> 00:47:12,830
I don't know where I should even go.

752
00:47:13,970 --> 00:47:17,540
Her aunt is the only family she has.
She has no friends either.

753
00:47:23,480 --> 00:47:26,250
Come to think of it,
I know nothing about Hui Gyeong.

754
00:47:28,920 --> 00:47:32,620
(Biseon, Gukhwa, Naega, Hwangcheong,
Oepo, Hwado, Seonsu)

755
00:47:32,690 --> 00:47:33,690
Yes, hello?

756
00:47:35,320 --> 00:47:36,330
Yes, ma'am.

757
00:47:38,460 --> 00:47:39,900
No, she hasn't been in touch.

758
00:47:40,330 --> 00:47:42,530
I found something in the locker
Hui Gyeong used.

759
00:47:42,970 --> 00:47:46,640
- What?
- I thought it was an old newspaper.

760
00:47:47,370 --> 00:47:50,670
She'd circled an ad for a hair salon
in the local paper.

761
00:47:51,210 --> 00:47:52,570
I'll send you a picture of it.

762
00:48:03,450 --> 00:48:05,290
(Kkakko-Ppokko Hair Salon)

763
00:48:06,290 --> 00:48:08,460
(Hair Salon for Rent,
Hair Salon - Urgent Sale)

764
00:48:09,890 --> 00:48:11,160
Salon for urgent sale.

765
00:48:12,490 --> 00:48:13,500
Ganghwa?

766
00:48:15,130 --> 00:48:16,130
Ganghwa?

767
00:48:29,610 --> 00:48:31,950
- All right, here we go.
- Yes.

768
00:48:35,420 --> 00:48:36,420
Catch.

769
00:48:36,650 --> 00:48:38,020
Here it comes!

770
00:48:38,850 --> 00:48:39,860
Nice!

771
00:48:41,690 --> 00:48:43,230
All right, we won!

772
00:48:44,560 --> 00:48:46,360
All right, just a little more,
and we've got this.

773
00:48:46,360 --> 00:48:47,400
- Okay.
- Yes.

774
00:48:49,560 --> 00:48:50,570
He got it.

775
00:48:54,600 --> 00:48:57,210
Amazing! Did you see that?

776
00:48:57,670 --> 00:48:59,880
- That was so cool.
- Again.

777
00:48:59,880 --> 00:49:01,640
- Go, Director!
- Yes.

778
00:49:02,140 --> 00:49:04,280
Is there anything
Director Yang can't do?

779
00:49:04,780 --> 00:49:05,780
I know, right?

780
00:49:07,880 --> 00:49:08,880
All right.

781
00:49:12,490 --> 00:49:15,320
- Now, pass!
- You're glad he's back, right?

782
00:49:20,030 --> 00:49:22,860
- Over there.
- Director Yang is sweating a lot.

783
00:49:23,430 --> 00:49:25,300
- Is there a towel anywhere?
- Okay, give me the ball.

784
00:49:31,310 --> 00:49:32,340
All right, here I go.

785
00:49:43,990 --> 00:49:45,150
Pacu Nacho!

786
00:49:46,190 --> 00:49:47,290
Where are you?

787
00:49:48,890 --> 00:49:50,690
- Director.
- Pacu Nacho!

788
00:49:55,960 --> 00:49:56,970
What the...

789
00:50:00,340 --> 00:50:02,370
Where on earth
did you find a place like this?

790
00:50:02,600 --> 00:50:06,010
- What? How did you find us?
- Director.

791
00:50:06,440 --> 00:50:10,310
You should've gotten our designers,
our best assets, a luxury hotel.

792
00:50:10,680 --> 00:50:12,110
Who was it?

793
00:50:12,550 --> 00:50:14,380
Who told the Vice President
where we were?

794
00:50:22,360 --> 00:50:23,430
Pro Jo?

795
00:50:24,030 --> 00:50:25,030
I'm sorry.

796
00:50:25,690 --> 00:50:29,900
- You spy.
- How could I say no to the VP?

797
00:50:30,270 --> 00:50:33,570
Unbelievable.
After all I did to keep it secret.

798
00:50:33,740 --> 00:50:34,740
Oh, look.

799
00:50:34,840 --> 00:50:38,040
Now that the Vice President is here,
we have enough for the portraits.

800
00:50:38,970 --> 00:50:41,280
- That's not the point right now...
- Pacu Nacho.

801
00:50:41,340 --> 00:50:42,340
What?

802
00:50:44,980 --> 00:50:48,350
- Don't look so unhappy in public.
- So evil.

803
00:50:48,620 --> 00:50:50,020
Who do you think you're fooling?

804
00:51:00,060 --> 00:51:01,060
Hello.

805
00:51:17,880 --> 00:51:18,910
Hey, hold on.

806
00:51:21,750 --> 00:51:25,650
- You have to dig like this.
- What's this? Is it a clam?

807
00:51:27,290 --> 00:51:29,190
Pacu Nacho, come over here.

808
00:51:29,320 --> 00:51:33,600
- This is so cool. Look at this.
- What is it?

809
00:51:33,860 --> 00:51:35,530
I've always wanted to do this.

810
00:51:36,770 --> 00:51:38,970
- Give it here. Hold it like this.
- Okay.

811
00:51:39,570 --> 00:51:43,140
- Here, this is how you do it.
- You're a natural. Show me again?

812
00:51:43,510 --> 00:51:44,670
You try.

813
00:51:48,040 --> 00:51:49,040
What was that?

814
00:51:49,950 --> 00:51:50,950
Goodness.

815
00:51:52,280 --> 00:51:54,820
- How? You do it then.
- No, don't.

816
00:52:04,360 --> 00:52:06,660
Thirty thousand dollars?
From Yang Dong Suk?

817
00:52:08,560 --> 00:52:10,300
It's all my savings
from my paychecks.

818
00:52:10,830 --> 00:52:14,870
Use that to pay for the stuff.
I'll earn the rest and pay you back.

819
00:52:15,170 --> 00:52:18,340
Wait, why are you giving this to me?

820
00:52:18,670 --> 00:52:21,380
I guess Ji Hu's Dad
really did take them.

821
00:52:22,210 --> 00:52:23,850
The merchandise
from the phone store is gone,

822
00:52:24,250 --> 00:52:26,850
and he even withdrew all the money
we'd saved up.

823
00:52:28,720 --> 00:52:30,150
The porridge is ready,

824
00:52:30,620 --> 00:52:31,990
so eat this
and get your strength back.

825
00:52:32,820 --> 00:52:34,090
You're not even surprised.

826
00:52:34,790 --> 00:52:37,230
You thought Ji Hu's Dad took it
from the beginning, didn't you?

827
00:52:37,860 --> 00:52:40,100
You thought so too, didn't you?

828
00:52:43,130 --> 00:52:45,900
So where are you going
all dressed up like this?

829
00:52:46,170 --> 00:52:47,800
I have to find that guy.

830
00:52:48,470 --> 00:52:49,700
Do you even know where he is?

831
00:52:51,740 --> 00:52:52,870
Like you said,

832
00:52:53,880 --> 00:52:55,840
I should have installed
a tracking app.

833
00:52:58,150 --> 00:52:59,250
Listen.

834
00:53:00,620 --> 00:53:02,980
I know this is really
shameless of me,

835
00:53:03,450 --> 00:53:05,320
but please don't let my father
and brother find out.

836
00:53:05,790 --> 00:53:08,690
I have no money. If I'm kicked out,
I'll have nowhere to go.

837
00:53:09,360 --> 00:53:13,700
If Dad finds out, he'll kick us out
and have Yong Gil thrown in jail.

838
00:53:15,200 --> 00:53:16,360
Is that what you're afraid of?

839
00:53:17,330 --> 00:53:18,400
He is still...

840
00:53:19,130 --> 00:53:21,200
Ji Hu's father, you know.

841
00:53:41,160 --> 00:53:43,160
(Seung Hui Hair Salon)

842
00:53:48,630 --> 00:53:50,470
Where on earth did you go,
Hui Gyeong?

843
00:53:52,100 --> 00:53:54,070
(For rent)

844
00:53:56,610 --> 00:53:58,040
You're unbelievable, Gong Dae Han.

845
00:53:58,940 --> 00:54:00,980
How can I be hungry
at a time like this?

846
00:54:03,410 --> 00:54:06,010
(Seong Tae Realty)

847
00:54:06,080 --> 00:54:08,120
She was thrilled that
a good person was taking over.

848
00:54:08,180 --> 00:54:09,620
- Really?
- Yes.

849
00:54:09,950 --> 00:54:13,290
- My gosh, I'm so excited!
- I'm sure you'll do great.

850
00:54:14,260 --> 00:54:15,520
Yes, Aunt.

851
00:54:15,990 --> 00:54:19,090
Hi, I'm Hui Gyeong's mother-in-law
over in Onjeong.

852
00:54:20,530 --> 00:54:23,770
I should have come in person,
but things have been so busy.

853
00:54:23,930 --> 00:54:25,300
So, how are you feeling?

854
00:54:25,770 --> 00:54:27,000
Me? Why do you ask?

855
00:54:27,900 --> 00:54:28,900
Pardon?

856
00:54:29,840 --> 00:54:32,240
I'd heard you were unwell.

857
00:54:33,140 --> 00:54:34,580
The kids went down to see you.

858
00:54:35,740 --> 00:54:37,780
I must've gotten it wrong.

859
00:54:41,350 --> 00:54:42,350
I see.

860
00:54:44,190 --> 00:54:46,390
Oh, so just Dae Han came by.

861
00:54:48,260 --> 00:54:50,160
All right, I understand.

862
00:55:04,440 --> 00:55:05,670
Yes, ma'am.

863
00:55:06,140 --> 00:55:08,180
I was just about to call you,
actually.

864
00:55:08,440 --> 00:55:11,780
Did you happen to speak with my son
yesterday or today?

865
00:55:12,110 --> 00:55:14,850
No, he hasn't called me.

866
00:55:15,450 --> 00:55:18,020
I see.
So, what were you calling about?

867
00:55:18,090 --> 00:55:21,820
If you're not taking the house,
I have another client interested.

868
00:55:22,960 --> 00:55:26,060
Yes, I suppose you should.

869
00:55:29,800 --> 00:55:32,330
- Welcome.
- Hi.

870
00:55:32,730 --> 00:55:35,770
Can I get a bottle of soju
and the usual, please?

871
00:55:36,270 --> 00:55:37,840
How come you're alone today?

872
00:55:38,310 --> 00:55:41,740
- You're always so lovey-dovey here.
- Tell me about it.

873
00:55:43,010 --> 00:55:44,150
Excuse me.

874
00:55:44,450 --> 00:55:47,880
- Another bottle of soju over here!
- Coming.

875
00:55:59,590 --> 00:56:00,660
Yes, Mom.

876
00:56:01,900 --> 00:56:04,370
I'm almost home. Yes.

877
00:56:06,130 --> 00:56:09,570
I'm meeting a friend for a drink,
so don't wait up.

878
00:56:10,470 --> 00:56:12,940
Okay. What?

879
00:56:13,270 --> 00:56:15,440
Of course. Hui Gyeong is doing fine.

880
00:56:16,980 --> 00:56:19,480
Yes. Don't worry,
just get some sleep.

881
00:56:20,650 --> 00:56:21,680
Okay.

882
00:56:45,610 --> 00:56:49,140
- What are you doing?
- Weren't you meeting a friend?

883
00:56:49,780 --> 00:56:50,810
Isn't that me?

884
00:56:51,880 --> 00:56:54,580
Who are you?
I don't share tables with strangers.

885
00:56:56,280 --> 00:56:58,620
- You don't recognize me, sweetie?
- "Sweetie?"

886
00:56:58,920 --> 00:57:01,260
That's creepy.
You look way older than me.

887
00:57:02,490 --> 00:57:06,430
It's me, Dong Suk.
I lived across the street from you,

888
00:57:06,490 --> 00:57:09,160
and I still work
just across the road...

889
00:57:09,230 --> 00:57:11,700
at the Korean medicine clinic.

890
00:57:11,800 --> 00:57:14,500
I'm Yang Dong Suk!

891
00:57:14,970 --> 00:57:16,200
And? So what?

892
00:57:18,070 --> 00:57:22,610
Remember how you'd carry my bag
on the way to piano lessons?

893
00:57:23,850 --> 00:57:27,550
You said it dragged on the ground
because I was too short,

894
00:57:27,620 --> 00:57:30,020
so you carried it for me every day.

895
00:57:30,820 --> 00:57:34,690
I don't think we're close enough
to be reminiscing like this.

896
00:57:36,760 --> 00:57:38,560
Just because we had a falling-out,

897
00:57:39,190 --> 00:57:41,560
it doesn't mean
the memories just disappear.

898
00:57:42,930 --> 00:57:44,500
Look, if you're this drunk,
you should just go home.

899
00:57:45,800 --> 00:57:46,870
Fine, I get it.

900
00:57:48,870 --> 00:57:53,510
Getting blown off wherever I go.
That's my life for you.

901
00:57:54,640 --> 00:57:56,240
Fine, I'll go.

902
00:57:57,280 --> 00:57:58,880
Hey!

903
00:57:59,180 --> 00:58:02,720
What's with you?
Hey, careful. Sit down.

904
00:58:04,790 --> 00:58:07,960
Why are you getting wasted alone?
What about your husband?

905
00:58:08,090 --> 00:58:09,090
Ji Hu's dad?

906
00:58:10,990 --> 00:58:12,030
He ran off.

907
00:58:12,790 --> 00:58:13,800
What?

908
00:58:13,860 --> 00:58:17,000
I thought he was scared
of getting kicked out,

909
00:58:17,000 --> 00:58:18,570
but he took off on his own.

910
00:58:19,400 --> 00:58:20,900
And this time,

911
00:58:21,600 --> 00:58:22,870
as if losing all our money
wasn't enough,

912
00:58:23,140 --> 00:58:25,070
he even stooped to stealing.

913
00:58:28,440 --> 00:58:29,610
You've really been through it...

914
00:58:31,680 --> 00:58:34,520
So what about you, Gong Dae Han?
Why are you drinking alone?

915
00:58:40,190 --> 00:58:41,490
You know...

916
00:58:45,290 --> 00:58:48,030
Did you know
your wife is cheating on you?

917
00:58:51,300 --> 00:58:53,870
- What did you say?
- I heard the whole thing.

918
00:58:54,270 --> 00:58:57,710
Your wife on the phone
with her lover.

919
00:58:58,240 --> 00:58:59,270
You...

920
00:59:00,040 --> 00:59:01,480
Watch your mouth.

921
00:59:01,810 --> 00:59:04,050
My Hui Gyeong is not like that,
you hear me?

922
00:59:04,680 --> 00:59:05,910
But it's true.

923
00:59:06,580 --> 00:59:09,680
"It feels like a dream, darling."

924
00:59:10,390 --> 00:59:11,390
That's what she said.

925
00:59:13,920 --> 00:59:16,360
When she's with you,

926
00:59:16,420 --> 00:59:19,130
she calls you "honey," right?
But she said...

927
00:59:19,760 --> 00:59:22,560
"My dear husband has no idea."

928
00:59:22,930 --> 00:59:26,070
- "See you tomorrow, darling."
- Hey!

929
00:59:26,130 --> 00:59:28,370
- You scared me!
- I've had enough of you... Darn it.

930
00:59:28,540 --> 00:59:30,000
What are you yelling for?

931
00:59:41,480 --> 00:59:42,820
Yes, Officer Jung.

932
00:59:42,850 --> 00:59:45,090
Yes, hi. Sorry it took me a while
to get back to you.

933
00:59:45,350 --> 00:59:47,420
I've been canvassing the area
all day.

934
00:59:47,560 --> 00:59:50,960
Don't worry about it.
I appreciate you looking into this.

935
00:59:52,030 --> 00:59:55,400
Well, I wasn't able
to find your wife.

936
00:59:55,700 --> 00:59:57,970
But I did find a lead.

937
00:59:58,370 --> 00:59:59,800
- A lead?
- Yes.

938
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:02,570
I'm at the convenience store
where I shop often.

939
01:00:02,800 --> 01:00:06,040
Apparently, the owner overheard
Ms. Lee Hui Gyeong...

940
01:00:06,040 --> 01:00:08,040
talking on the phone with someone.

941
01:00:08,680 --> 01:00:11,950
Who was she on the phone with?

942
01:00:12,010 --> 01:00:14,250
No, I mean, what did she say?

943
01:00:14,980 --> 01:00:18,320
Well, the thing is...

944
01:00:18,750 --> 01:00:21,120
It's all right.
Just tell me, Officer Jung.

945
01:00:21,360 --> 01:00:24,060
Apparently, this is what she said.

946
01:00:24,790 --> 01:00:28,160
"Pick me up at the convenience store
at Gongsan Junction, darling."

947
01:00:29,800 --> 01:00:30,800
What...

948
01:00:31,770 --> 01:00:34,000
- "Darling?"
- See?

949
01:00:34,470 --> 01:00:37,210
I told you she said "darling."

950
01:00:39,070 --> 01:00:40,240
Well...

951
01:00:42,380 --> 01:00:46,510
- Are you sure?
- Yes. The store owner...

952
01:00:47,150 --> 01:00:50,180
showed me CCTV footage of her
getting into a car.

953
01:00:50,690 --> 01:00:53,590
It's a bit grainy,
so you can't see the face, but...

954
01:00:53,920 --> 01:00:57,430
it looks like she left with a man.

955
01:00:57,930 --> 01:00:58,930
I see.

956
01:01:00,430 --> 01:01:03,560
I understand. Okay, all right.

957
01:01:17,810 --> 01:01:19,580
You should have known better.

958
01:01:20,750 --> 01:01:25,590
You're from a family of doctors,
and you're a physical therapist.

959
01:01:26,420 --> 01:01:29,560
Why marry a girl with no background,
who's not even in your league,

960
01:01:29,620 --> 01:01:32,460
all because she's pretty?

961
01:01:45,340 --> 01:01:46,940
At least I'm better off.

962
01:01:48,840 --> 01:01:52,250
Ji Hu's dad...
At least he never cheated.

963
01:01:58,890 --> 01:02:00,050
Dae Han?

964
01:02:01,590 --> 01:02:02,590
- Hey, Seong Mi.
- My gosh.

965
01:02:03,190 --> 01:02:05,030
- What...
- I...

966
01:02:05,560 --> 01:02:08,530
- My goodness.
- The person I respect the most.

967
01:02:08,600 --> 01:02:13,500
Goodness, you've had a lot to drink.
Didn't Hui Gyeong visit her family?

968
01:02:13,730 --> 01:02:14,740
Yes.

969
01:02:16,300 --> 01:02:17,310
Seong Mi.

970
01:02:18,210 --> 01:02:19,370
I'm so sorry.

971
01:02:20,340 --> 01:02:21,910
I'm really sorry.

972
01:02:22,880 --> 01:02:24,610
What are you sorry for?

973
01:02:24,980 --> 01:02:26,610
I'm pretty sure Hui Gyeong...

974
01:02:28,650 --> 01:02:30,520
might have run off with the money.

975
01:02:31,620 --> 01:02:34,360
- What?
- I think she was seeing someone.

976
01:02:35,120 --> 01:02:39,160
- Wait, what are you talking about?
- Hui Gyeong was having an affair.

977
01:02:40,090 --> 01:02:42,230
She had an affair
and ran off behind my back.

978
01:02:43,260 --> 01:02:44,600
She was cheating on me.

979
01:02:45,270 --> 01:02:47,940
She just up and left.
Just like my father...

980
01:02:48,270 --> 01:02:49,300
She just...

981
01:02:49,300 --> 01:02:50,300
Dae Han.

982
01:02:53,240 --> 01:02:55,110
Seong Mi, wait. Seong Mi...

983
01:02:55,940 --> 01:02:57,040
I have a favor to ask.

984
01:02:58,510 --> 01:03:01,920
Promise not to tell Mom
and Jeong Han. Okay?

985
01:03:02,420 --> 01:03:04,850
If Mom and Jeong Han find out,
they'll be heartbroken...

986
01:03:07,960 --> 01:03:11,690
Mom might collapse again,
so please just keep it a secret.

987
01:03:12,690 --> 01:03:14,160
Collapse over what?

988
01:03:48,760 --> 01:03:51,370
(Recipe For Love)

989
01:03:51,430 --> 01:03:54,770
When I was little,
a friend was going to study abroad,

990
01:03:54,840 --> 01:03:56,470
so I made this as a farewell gift.

991
01:03:56,540 --> 01:03:59,210
By any chance, was that person
your first love, Ju Ah?

992
01:04:00,540 --> 01:04:03,910
Dr. Gong was treating Dr. Yang
like a bratty little kid,

993
01:04:03,980 --> 01:04:05,050
and just bullying him relentlessly.

994
01:04:05,110 --> 01:04:07,980
That's rich,
from the one begging for a job.

995
01:04:08,120 --> 01:04:09,820
You have proof?

996
01:04:09,880 --> 01:04:13,550
Someone recently taught me
the importance of having proof.

997
01:04:13,750 --> 01:04:16,860
You absolutely have to get
Dr. Gong's phone.

998
01:04:17,120 --> 01:04:19,760
Float like a butterfly,
sting like a bee.

999
01:04:19,930 --> 01:04:22,860
You have to get a divorce.
You can't go on like this.

1000
01:04:23,560 --> 01:04:25,000
I don't recognize this number.

1001
01:04:27,200 --> 01:04:28,440
Hello? Who is this?
